{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-chapter-level-2-chapter-level-2-tsx","path":"/topics/bruising/diagnosis/differential-diagnosis/","result":{"pageContext":{"chapter":{"id":"a1d489d6-6858-5cd0-8d4d-bab0c0e89ca7","slug":"differential-diagnosis","fullItemName":"Differential diagnosis","depth":2,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field 69ea211c-97d0-4f15-958b-a12bc2a93707 --><h2>What else might it be?</h2><!-- end field 69ea211c-97d0-4f15-958b-a12bc2a93707 -->","summary":"","htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item fba38df1-4efc-448a-b206-0e90e2f33391 --><!-- begin field 0e70c225-b1d0-4004-bbb0-205dfba14845 --><ul><li><strong>Skin conditions which might be mistaken for bruising include:</strong><ul><li><strong>Linear eruptions</strong><ul><li>Allergic contact dermatitis.  See the CKS topic on <a class=\"topic-reference external-reference\" href=\"/topics/dermatitis-contact/\">Dermatitis - contact</a> for more information.</li><li>Phytophotodermatitis — an inflammatory and pigmentary reaction of the skin to light, following contact with phototoxic substances from certain plants, such as giant hogweed.</li><li>Stretch marks (striae).</li></ul></li><li><strong>Non-linear eruptions</strong><ul><li>Slate-grey naevi (Mongolian blue spots) — macular blue-grey non-tender macules present at birth on the sacrum and buttocks in normal dark-skinned infants.</li><li>Haemangiomas — benign congenital cutaneous tumours.</li><li>Urticaria pigmentosa — numerous reddish-brown or pale maculopapules, plaques, or nodules which urticate within a few minutes of gentle rubbing. They are distributed symmetrically usually on the trunk and thighs, but can present anywhere on the body, sparing the face, palms, and soles. </li><li>Dermatitis artefacta — self-inflicted skin lesions.</li><li>Congenital vascular naevi.</li></ul></li><li><strong>Other</strong><ul><li>Skin staining from dye or ink.</li></ul></li></ul></li></ul><!-- end field 0e70c225-b1d0-4004-bbb0-205dfba14845 --><!-- end item fba38df1-4efc-448a-b206-0e90e2f33391 -->","topic":{"id":"0695329d-6789-5f2e-bdd4-23fa7e538a68","topicId":"a2ffbaff-593f-430e-ba07-22a88a81554f","topicName":"Bruising","slug":"bruising","lastRevised":"Last revised in March 2016","chapters":[{"id":"cd3da1a8-ef20-5a0a-b9ee-42193acd5123","fullItemName":"Summary","slug":"summary","subChapters":[]},{"id":"23fb83e3-3c5a-52f9-abe6-74a66bb0fbdd","fullItemName":"Have I got the right topic?","slug":"have-i-got-the-right-topic","subChapters":[]},{"id":"07d092b9-1fc7-5bde-b6fd-0844b88c2e2d","fullItemName":"How up-to-date is this topic?","slug":"how-up-to-date-is-this-topic","subChapters":[{"id":"690311f9-d70d-5981-a8c1-217bbb32f72b","slug":"changes","fullItemName":"Changes"},{"id":"6c40fbc1-a0ca-53e5-ac89-9092d1659ad3","slug":"update","fullItemName":"Update"}]},{"id":"97948439-efdb-5ee7-a48d-1a8021361f1c","fullItemName":"Goals and outcome measures","slug":"goals-outcome-measures","subChapters":[{"id":"63d16865-3aee-5e25-84e7-fadaaa1cb8d2","slug":"goals","fullItemName":"Goals"},{"id":"5139834d-a623-5be5-9d54-877a38c4327e","slug":"outcome-measures","fullItemName":"Outcome measures"},{"id":"48d78c1e-438d-56eb-9e93-9293df84a7cf","slug":"audit-criteria","fullItemName":"Audit criteria"},{"id":"158558ee-e252-5417-ae7e-077c116eb209","slug":"qof-indicators","fullItemName":"QOF indicators"},{"id":"cab2f1e3-cd8f-56df-b443-870cbd98a642","slug":"qipp-options-for-local-implementation","fullItemName":"QIPP - Options for local implementation"},{"id":"70808409-cc3d-5593-be7a-f8e075532837","slug":"nice-quality-standards","fullItemName":"NICE Quality standards"}]},{"id":"929c1597-f2e2-5a0c-a69a-7a95d4e5811e","fullItemName":"Background information","slug":"background-information","subChapters":[{"id":"f5d9ef3b-09a0-5d56-a336-565b172723d3","slug":"definition","fullItemName":"Definition"},{"id":"79a0bd9a-336c-5520-9f3c-182c0f8e7639","slug":"causes","fullItemName":"Causes"}]},{"id":"d96a506d-aba4-5d50-9b4b-d7b731a31893","fullItemName":"Diagnosis","slug":"diagn